The transmission and new capture data were analyzed
in the resolved resonance region using the multilevel
R-matrix code sammy. Direct and resonance part of
cross sections, determined using measured resonance
properties, were averaged over Maxwellian spectrum
with given temperature to get the Maxwellian average
dominant in resonance part of xs.

x4freetext: Neutron energy was determined using the TOF
technique. ORELA operated with a repetition rate of
525 Hz, 8-ns pulse width, and an average power of 6 KW.
The energies in the crunch table are calculated
by non-relativistic kinematics while the energies in
the data section are calculated by relativistic
kinematics from the TOF at the center of the bin.
Normalized to the 4.9 eV Au resonance. Pulse height
weighting technique applied with the neutron binding
Corrected for experimental effects such as dead time,
efficiency and known backgrounds. Not corrected for
finite sample related effects such as self shielding
